cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with deep learning representation for 3D shape recognition, which is a visual application. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with 3D shape retrieval, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of autoencoder for feature learning is a machine learning technique, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of limited number of 3D shapes for feature learning, which requires the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the aggregation of features learned on 2D images, which is a multimedia application (cs.MM).
